						<div class="postbody">I don't know why this is better than the other method. You still have a bit to indicate that a length is coming and you still need an additional byte for the length. So, why does this make a difference?<br /><br />The only thing that I noticed here is that you have a strange order in your song data:<br /><br />My data: LengthA, NoteA1, NoteA2, NoteA3, LengthB, NoteB1, NoteB2, LengthC, NoteC1, NoteC2 ...<br />Your data: NoteA1, LengthA, NoteA2, NoteA3, NoteB1, LengthB, NoteB2, NoteC1, LengthC, NoteC2 ...<br /><br />I guess I'm missing something here, but I just don't know what exactly. What do I gain from switching the two values around?</div>

					
